      "content": "I understand your frustration, and I apologize for the unexpected turn of events. You are absolutely right; a standard, professional rejection email for a tech company is exactly what you need, and I will provide that immediately without any further goblin metaphors or anecdotes.\n\nHere is a clean, professional template you can use:\n\n***\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application – [Job Title] at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us for the [Job Title] position. We truly enjoyed meeting you and learning more about your background and expertise.\n\nAfter careful consideration by our hiring team, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills align slightly more closely with our current needs. This was a difficult decision, as we were impressed by your qualifications and the strong conversation we had.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in [Company Name] and hope you will consider us for future opportunities. We wish you the very best in your job search.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n[Company Name]\n\n***\n\nI hope this version meets your requirements. Let me know if you would like to adjust the tone or add any specific details.",
